      • LCPassport

        public LCPassport()
        Constructs a new LCPassport with no data in it. A LCUser constructed in this way will not have an objectId and will not persist to the database until LCPassportManager.signUp() is called.

        public boolean isAuthenticated()
        Whether the LCPassport has been authenticated on this device. This will be true if the LCPassport was obtained via a loginInBackground or signUp method. Only an authenticated LCPassport can be saved (with altered attributes) and deleted.
